ERCOT deal from JMF Heads up for you on ERCOTImbalance deal from had a price associated with it I have zeroed out this out but thought you needed to know Thanks MJ

RE MCP revisions Cc Hey Joe It usually takes about a week after flow date for ERCOT to put out a revision file for that day I will check it first thing Monday morning as well as put in a dispute to make sure that ERCOT is reviewing this interval price I will update you as soon as I find anything out thanks for the heads up MJ Original Message From Capasso Joe Sent Sat PM To Jacobson Michael Forney John M Cc Subject MCP revisions Michael The Hourly Ercot desk had a long position in the Ercot Pool on October th for hour The final interval for came in negative at I checked in the Ercot website but it has not been revised Can we dispute the MCP settlement price Here is a little more information At on Oct th Ercot called all of the QSEs and said that the computer systems would be going down They said that the systems should be down for about minutes This means that the computer systems were not even on throughout the entire interval When it came back on line the neg print occurred for all three zones It is very unusual for all three zones to print negative for the same interval We might have a chance for a realistic revision Any help is appreciated Thanks Joe C

RE Constellation DisputeThe deal number is under your name but I think that it is Erics Thanks Original Message From Forney John M Sent Monday November PM To Jacobson Michael Subject RE Constellation Dispute sure who is the trader listed on the deal Original Message From Jacobson Michael Sent Monday November PM To Forney John M Cc Grace Rebecca M Subject Constellation Dispute JMF Constellation is disputing this sale we show to them in EnPower as well as the Hourly PL I have nothing to give them for support can you help me out or at least pass this along to whomever did the deal HE mw Thanks MJ

RE Constellation Dispute Cc Thanks for your help with solving this discrepancy we finally got CPS to agree with our numbers Thanks again MJ Original Message From Phillips George Sent Monday November PM To Forney John M Capasso Joe Cc Jacobson Michael Subject RE Constellation Dispute Deal number was a sale to Constellation as follows MWs Traders name Tyler HE South Zone Please leave me a message if I can answer any other questions JohnJoe I am not certain of Michael Jacobsons email address from home could please forward this message Original Message From Forney John M Sent Mon PM To Phillips George Capasso Joe Cc Subject FW Constellation Dispute Can you guys check this out Constellation is an important counterparty and we want to get them an answer pretty soon Im sure you guys are correct but if you can provide some detail about their trader name etc that would be helpful Thanks JMF Original Message From Jacobson Michael Sent Monday November PM To Forney John M Subject RE Constellation Dispute The deal number is under your name but I think that it is Erics Thanks Original Message From Forney John M Sent Monday November PM To Jacobson Michael Subject RE Constellation Dispute sure who is the trader listed on the deal Original Message From Jacobson Michael Sent Monday November PM To Forney John M Cc Grace Rebecca M Subject Constellation Dispute JMF Constellation is disputing this sale we show to them in EnPower as well as the Hourly PL I have nothing to give them for support can you help me out or at least pass this along to whomever did the deal HE mw Thanks MJ

RE Revised mcpe for interval Sir Forney This interval MCPE has been changed from to for MJ Original Message From Forney John M Sent Thursday November PM To Jacobson Michael Subject Revised mcpe for interval The has been deemed questionable Can you follow up to see if this is going to be revised Thanks JMF

LCRA discrepancy Cc JMF I have a discrepancy with LCRA on The following notes are in the PL The original deal was a buy from LCRA and a sale to RESI but LCRA did not enter into Portal in time Therefore the purchase was made from the ERCOT Imbal market where it was purchased for The initials in the PL are GTP We show this in the system as an ERCOTImbalance purchase and a sale to Reliant however LCRA claims that we should show this purchase from them Please pass this along to the appropriate trader to clear up the discrepancy Thanks MJ

RE Frontera for tomorrow Cc Hey John Thanks for the heads up FYI I found an hourly ERCOTImbalance deal from yesterday with a price on it Ive zeroed out the price but I wanted to let you know so you can pass the word on Deal mws HE Thanks Michael Original Message From Forney John M Sent Monday October PM To Grace Rebecca M Jacobson Michael Subject Frontera for tomorrow Frontera will be running short for the schedule listed below I have sold them this imbalance for Any imbalance charges billed to them should be allocated to me listed on the schedule below hour ending he he he he he The total is This is the equivalent of a financial swap but the settlement will remain intact Thanks JMF
ERCOT deal with CPSB Cc Hey Steve CPSB is not showing a deal that we have in EnPower do you have anything that I can give them to support this deal HE mws Thanks Michael

ERCOT counterparties Cc John Per our conversation yesterday this is an email to clarify the ERCOT counterparty names that are in EnPower ERCOT Imbalance ERCOTIMBA this counterparty is for commodities must select a delivery point and have a zero price EPMIERCOTPOOL EPMIERCOT this counterparty is for transmission only zero price Electric Reliability Council of Texas Inc ERCOT this counterparty is for interdesk annuities Thanks Michael x

Transmission Rates Cc Hey guys Ive updated the transmission rates table for May here is the location MElectricEast Volume MgmtTransmissionTransmission Rates If there is a better spot for this to make it more accessible just let me know and I can put a copy of it whereever Couple of other trends Ive noticed that hopefully can be corrected First Energy transmission is now and has been for a while under the counterparty American Transmission Systems Inc ATSI Duke transmission should be under the Duke counterparty Duke Electric Transmission DUKEELETRA Georgias ancillary service charges have changed although their website has not be updated price changed from to Please pass this along to the rest of the group if any of you have any questions or suggestions dont hesitate to call Thanks Michael AOL IM mejake steno x

BPWRI cut from June Cc Hey Juan BP has brought this cut back again claiming that you agreed to keep their purchase whole however WRI does not agree to booking out Per Karen at BP you agreed to a bookout price for HE from tag sourcesink EES I have a copy of the tag at my desk in case you dont want to go digging through the tag archives Please look into this as soon as you can this has been going on way too long and I have exhausted my resources in solving the issue Thanks Michael x
